def: To separate, as things mixed. Bacon.
Of or pertaining to twenty; consisting of twenty.
Consisting of loam; partaking of the nature of loam; resemblingloam. Bacon.
The American golden plover. [Local, U. S.]
A universal proposition. See Subaltern, 2. Whately.
Erroneous conception; false opinion; wrong understanding.Harvey.
Pertaining to both the tongue and the pharynx; -- appliedespecially to the ninth pair of cranial nerves, which are distributedto the pharynx and tongue.-- n. One of the glossopharyngeal nerves.
Excruciated; tortured.And here my heart long time excruciate. Chapman.
Cleaving or sticking like wax. Cotgrave.
One who invents or finds out something new; a contriver;especially, one who invents mechanical devices.
